xxl.core.math.statistics.nonparametric.aggregates

Class EmpiricalCDFAggregateFunction

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.math.functions.AggregationFunction<Number[],EmpiricalCDF>
      • xxl.core.math.statistics.nonparametric.aggregates.EmpiricalCDFAggregateFunction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, OnlineAggregation

    public class EmpiricalCDFAggregateFunction
extends AggregationFunction<Number[],EmpiricalCDF>
implements OnlineAggregation
    In the context of online aggregation, running aggregates are built. Given an iterator of data, an Aggregator computes iteratively aggregates. For instance, the current maximum of the already processed data is determined. An internal aggregation function processes the computation of the new element by consuming the old aggregate and the new element from the input cursor. Generally, each aggregation function must support a function call of the following type:
    agg_n = f (agg_n-1, next).
    There, agg_n denotes the computed aggregation value after n steps, f represents the aggregation function, agg_n-1 the computed aggregation value after n-1 steps and next the next object to use for computation.
    This class implements an aggregation function that computes the empirical cumulative distribution function. Given an old and a new sample as processed objects, this function computes the empirical cdf based on the new sample.
    Consider the following example that displays a concrete application of a empirical cdf aggregation function combined with an aggregator: 
            Aggregator aggregator =
                        new Aggregator(
                                new Aggregator( input, mapSamplingStrategy (sampleSize, samplingType)),
                                new EmpiricalCDFAggregateFunction()
                        );
    See Also:
    Aggregator, AdaptiveAggregationFunction, Aggregators, EmpiricalCDF, Serialized Form

    • Method Detail

      • invoke

        public EmpiricalCDF invoke(EmpiricalCDF old,
                           Number[] next)
        Two-figured function call for supporting aggregation by this function. Each aggregation function must support a function call like agg_n = f (agg_n-1, next), where agg_n denotes the computed aggregation value after n steps, f the aggregation function, agg_n-1 the computed aggregation value after n-1 steps and next the next object to use for computation. This method delivers only null as aggregation result as long as the aggregation has not yet initialized. As result of the aggregation the empirical cdf, that relies on the current block, is returned.
        Specified by:
        invoke in class AggregationFunction<Number[],EmpiricalCDF>
        Parameters:
        old - result of the aggregation function in the previous computation step
        next - next object used for computation
        Returns:
        aggregation value after n steps (an empirical cdf
